  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-1.n-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-1.n-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-1.n-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-1.n-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-1.n-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> pepper strips</strong>, <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 8-10 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-2.n-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-2.n-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-2.n-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-2.n-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-2.n-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your<strong> ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>arborio rice</strong> and stir to fully coat the grains and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-3.n-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-3.n-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-3.n-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-3.n-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-3.n-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[700ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[900ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong>, then add to the pan</p><p>Bring to the boil then reduce the heat to low</p><p>Cook, covered, for an initial 20-25 min or until the rice is tender and has absorbed most of the liquid</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-4.n-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-4.n-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-4.n-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-4.n-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-4.n-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After 20-25 min, drain, then add your<strong> king</strong> <strong>prawns</strong> and cook covered for a further 4-5 min or until the prawns are cooked through</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-5.n-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-5.n-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-5.n-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-5.n-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-5.n-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> into quarters</p><p>Combine a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice </strong>with your <strong>mayo</strong> and a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>lemon aioli</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-6.n-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-6.n-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-6.n-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-6.n-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-6.n-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the prawns are cooked through, remove the pan from the heat and add the<strong> </strong>juice of <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lemon quarter[s]</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>parsley</strong> (save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and season with plenty of <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your<strong> king prawn paella</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-7.n-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-7.n-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-7.n-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-7.n-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/496.-step-7.n-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drizzle the<strong> lemon aioli</strong> over the<strong> king prawn paella</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> remaining chopped</strong> <strong>parsley</strong> and <strong>remaining lemon quarters</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
